### Parcel Management Tests

### 1. Create a new parcel (requires authentication)
POST http://localhost:3000/parcel
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "recipientName": "Alice Johnson",
  "recipientEmail": "alice@example.com",
  "recipientPhone": "+1234567890",
  "pickupAddress": "123 Main St, City, State 12345",
  "deliveryAddress": "456 Oak Ave, City, State 12345",
  "weight": "2.5kg",
  "description": "Fragile electronics package"
}

### 2. Get all parcels (admin only)
GET http://localhost:3000/parcel
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 3. Get parcels by user (authenticated user)
GET http://localhost:3000/parcel/user
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 4. Get parcels by driver (driver only)
GET http://localhost:3000/parcel/driver
Authorization: Bearer {{driverToken}}

### 5. Get parcel by ID
GET http://localhost:3000/parcel/1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 6. Update parcel status
PATCH http://localhost:3000/parcel/1/status
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{driverToken}}

{
  "status": "IN_TRANSIT"
}

### 7. Assign driver to parcel (admin only)
PATCH http://localhost:3000/parcel/1/assign-driver
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "driverId": 1
}

### 8. Get parcel statistics (admin only)
GET http://localhost:3000/parcel/stats
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 9. Public tracking (no auth required)
GET http://localhost:3000/parcel/track/{{trackingNumber}}

### 10. Create another parcel for testing
POST http://localhost:3000/parcel
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

